__gt_http_dd_//playground.babylonjs.com/#21TQJT#35_lt_/a_gt_\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tI put an empty ._lt_em_gt_subMeshes_lt_/em_gt_ array on each ground-tile_co_ so the _lt_em_gt__lt_a href_eq__qt_https_dd_//github.com/BabylonJS/Babylon.js/blob/master/src/Mesh/babylon.mesh.js#L1304_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_convertToFlatShadedMesh_lt_/a_gt_()_lt_/em_gt_ works again.  Then I sent a bunch of before/after length-of-normals-array values... to console.  I think it takes 4 directional lights to light this properly... so I added all 4... and tried to set their directions wisely.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tBecause of my professional lighting prowess (yeeeah_co_ right)... the _lt_a href_eq__qt_http_dd_//playground.babylonjs.com/#21TQJT%2336_qt_ rel_eq__qt_external nofollow_qt__gt_no-gap version_lt_/a_gt_ looks... somewhat seamless. \n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tEach tile is 867 verts (and normals) before conversion_co_ 4608 after.  5.3 times larger!  woah.  That seems too much_co_ but I know little about the conversion algo.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tSo_co_ for now_co_ we_t_ll hope... that at a basic edge-point... there are (no more than...) 3 verts.  But there may be 4.  The original vert/normal... might have been repeated.  (explaining the &gt_sm_ triple vert-count increase).  We can_t_t see the repeat-of-original verts/normals in the scene_co_ because their normal lines are laid precisely atop the original.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tIf there ARE four verts where one vert previously was positioned_co_ then there will be 16 verts/normals to process at every 4-way intersection.  Let_t_s look at a scenario.  Let_t_s pretend we are about to process the first (original) vert (of maybe 4 total) found at the southeast corner position of tile 0x0.  We need to find the ORIGINAL corner-verts that are on the tiles east_co_ southeast_co_ and south of this point_co_ average all 4 together_co_ and put them back.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tLater in the iteration_co_ we do the same with the _lt_u_gt_first_lt_/u_gt_ ADDED vert/normal at that location_co_ and average it with the _lt_u_gt_first_lt_/u_gt_ ADDED point at the other three corners.  Then later in the iteration_co_ we_t_ll hit the _lt_u_gt_second_lt_/u_gt_ added vert_co_ and average it with the _lt_u_gt_second_lt_/u_gt_ added verts on the other three corners.  Then the _lt_u_gt_third_lt_/u_gt_ added verts/normals... and pray like hell there_t_s not a FOURTH added vert there.  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_smile.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/smile@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt_  OUCH!\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tAll in all_co_ if we expect our normals _qt_sewing machine_qt_ to work on flat shaded grounds... um... we are going to get some fresh tumors... designing it.  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_o_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_ohmy.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/ohmy@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__dd_o_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt_  Pseudo_dd_\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\t- retrieve a point along a mated edge_lt_br /_gt_\n\t- retrieve its cross-seam mate ( but..._lt_strong_gt_ _lt_/strong_gt_how do we determine_lt_strong_gt_ which_lt_/strong_gt_ vert/normal... of the possible FOUR verts positioned there... is the correct mate?  erf! )_lt_br /_gt_\n\t- do the averaging_lt_br /_gt_\n\t- stow/write the new averaged-normals values... somewhere_lt_br /_gt_\n\t- rinse/repeat... way too many times.\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tI guess the other option would be... make sure you run the sewing machine FIRST_co_ and later (as wanted)... do the conversion to flat shaded.  I think that would be wiser than trying to build a post-conversion-ready sewing machine.  erf.  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_ src_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/default_smile.png_qt_ srcset_eq__qt_http_dd_//www.html5gamedevs.com/uploads/emoticons/smile@2x.png 2x_qt_ title_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ width_eq__qt_20_qt_ /_gt__lt_/p_gt_\n\n\n\t\t\t\n\t\t_lt_/div_gt_\n\n\t\t_lt_div class_eq__qt_ipsI_qt__gt__lt_/div_gt__lt_/div_gt_"},{"Owner":"Wingnut","Date":"2016-08-24T02:51:42Z","Content":"_lt_div class_eq__qt_mages_qt__gt_\n\t\t\t\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tStatus_dd_  For those following-along at home_co_ I started working on some pieces of the normals sewing machine.  To quickly re-brief... when we remove the gaps between the tiles_co_ we have good heightMap seam-less-ness_co_ but we noticed that the NORMALS for verts on ONE seam mate... don_t_t match the normals for the matching vert on the other side of the seam.  SO_co_ we have lighting discolorations at the seams (when gaps are removed - see line 277). \n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tWe (I) seek to grab the normal at each point along the seam_co_ reach across the seam and grab the mating-vert_t_s normal_co_ average their values together_co_ and put them both back.  This should remove the lighting discoloration at the seams. \n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tAt each 4-way corner of tiles_co_ FOUR normals will be average together and written back to the mesh geometry... instead of just two.  This is an important point (ar ar ar)... .because we could accidentally do repeat/incomplete averaging of 4-way corner normals.  The normals at each 4-way might need temp storage_co_ then let the X seams get averaged_co_ then the Z seams get averaged_co_ and THEN average the temp-stowed 4-pack of corner normals... and put them back... overwriting any normals-adjusting that the X and Z along-the-entire-seam sewings... previously did.  Wow_co_ huh?\n_lt_/p_gt_\n\n_lt_p_gt_\n\tWas that a _qt_quick re-brief_qt_?  Erf!  _lt_img alt_eq__qt__dd_)_qt_ data-emoticon_eq__qt__qt_ height_eq__qt_20_qt_